
***LARAVEL FRAMEWORK***

1. Need php version greater than 7.0.0
	# php -v ---checking php version

2. Need Composer (dependencies manager)		

// Install PHP Composer

	1.Update your packages:
		#sudo apt-get update

	2.Install the curl utility:
		#sudo apt-get install curl

	3.Download the installer:
		#sudo curl -s https://getcomposer.org/installer | php

	4.Move the composer.phar file to required directory:
		#sudo mv composer.phar (required directory)

Use the composer command to test the installation. If Composer is installed correctly, the server will respond with a long list of help information and commands:

user@localhost:~# composer
