                /_/
......
......

Reference: https://www.1and1.com/cloud-community/learn/application/php/install-and-use-php-composer-on-ubuntu-1604/

3. Instalation of laravel
	using composer
		#composer create-project --prefer-dist laravel/laravel (Project Name)
4.configuration setting
	Make bootstrap and storage file writable
		Then first rename .env.example to .env
			and set application key
				 #php artisan key:generate

			

Advantages of laravel: 
Reference: https://belitsoft.com/laravel-development-services/10-benefits-using-laravel-php-framework



## when we are using ckeditor package

asset(vendor/../../..)
was not working 
so changed the permission of the file using sudo chmod -R 777 vendor/
and run php artisan vendor:publish --provider="Unisharp\Ckeditor\ServiceProvider" this command 
after this it will add all the js css to the public file . 









 
























